The paper deals with the problem of joint downlink and uplink user association and beamforming in a cloud radio access network (C-RAN) to minimize energy consumption. This involves optimizing the allocation of resources to mobile users and access points, which is a common problem in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking (cs.NI), and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of interactive applications with stringent uplink requirements, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes algorithms for solving the optimization problem, which involves computational complexity and algorithms (cs.DC).
